{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix SSB start symbol calculation for 60 kHz subcarrier spacing\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_ssb_start_symbol()` function in the NR MAC common module was missing support for 60 kHz subcarrier spacing, causing incorrect SSB scheduling in FR2 bands. When called with `scs = NR_SubcarrierSpacing_kHz60`, the function would fall through to the default case and trigger an assertion failure, preventing proper SSB transmission.\n\nAdditionally, the function lacked bounds checking for the `i_ssb` parameter, which could lead to out-of-bounds array access when invalid SSB indices were provided. This could result in unpredictable behavior or crashes during SSB scheduling.\n\nThe fix adds the missing case for 60 kHz SCS, implements proper bounds validation for all SSB patterns, and ensures correct SSB position calculation according to 38.213 specifications.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_COMMON/nr_mac_common.c`: \n  - Added missing case for `NR_SubcarrierSpacing_kHz60` in `get_ssb_start_symbol()`\n  - Implemented bounds checking for `i_ssb` parameter for all SCS values\n  - Added AssertFatal checks to prevent invalid array accesses\n  - Updated function to correctly handle FR2 SSB patterns (Type B with 64 SSBs max for 60 kHz)\n"
}